# Railway Environment Variables Configuration

Copy these environment variables to your Railway project:

## Required Variables

```
SECRET_KEY=<generate-new-secret-key>
DEBUG=False
DJANGO_SETTINGS_MODULE=camera_demo_backend.settings
```

## Database
Railway will automatically set this when you add PostgreSQL:
```
DATABASE_URL=<automatically-set-by-railway>
```

## Hosts & CORS
```
ALLOWED_HOSTS=.railway.app
CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://your-frontend-domain.vercel.app
CSRF_TRUSTED_ORIGINS=https://your-frontend-domain.vercel.app
```

## Generate SECRET_KEY

Run this command to generate a secure SECRET_KEY:

```bash
python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_urlsafe(50))"
```

## How to Set in Railway

1. Go to your Railway project dashboard
2. Click on your service
3. Go to "Variables" tab
4. Click "New Variable"
5. Add each variable above
6. Railway will automatically redeploy

## After Setting Variables

1. Railway will rebuild and redeploy
2. Create superuser: Use Railway's shell feature
3. Test your backend at: `https://your-app.railway.app`
